text: Kamel Lemoui (28 February 1939 – 3 January 2022) was an Algerian football player and manager. He played RC Paris B, Béziers, US Biskra, MC Alger, CR Belcourt, Olympique de Médéa and JS El Biar. He also played for the Algerian national team between 1963 and 1968. He would also manage the national team for a year between 1988 and 1989. Lemoui died from COVID-19 on 3 January 2022, during the COVID-19 pandemic in France in Paris at age 82.L’ancien sélectionneur national Kamel Lemoui emporté par le Covid-19 ==References== Category:1939 births Category:2022 deaths Category:Algerian football managers Category:Algerian footballers Category:Deaths from the COVID-19 pandemic in Paris
